 the selection by instantiating the candidate and computing any nested obligations that must also be satisfied. For user-defined impls, this means calling `confirm_impl_candidate()` which further applies the `rematch_impl()` method at line 442 of mod.rs.\n\n**ObligationForest Data Structure** (rustc_data_structures/src/obligation_forest/mod.rs): The fulfillment engine uses an ObligationForest (defined at line 152) as a tree-based data structure to track outstanding obligations. Each node tracks its obligation state, dependents, and parents. The forest efficiently manages cycles and dependencies among obligations.\n\n**FulfillmentContext Integration** (compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/fulfill.rs): The FulfillmentContext struct at line 61 encapsulates an ObligationForest of PendingPredicateObligations. It drives the overall trait obligation resolution process by repeatedly processing obligations through the FulfillProcessor (line 252), which invokes SelectionContext::poly_select() at line 853. The `process_obligations()` method of ObligationForest at line 433 of obligation_forest/mod.rs returns ProcessResult enums (line 143): Unchanged (ambiguous), Changed (with subobligations), or Error.\n\n**Error Reporting** (compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/error_reporting/traits/mod.rs): When obligations fail, `report_fulfillment_errors()` at line 140 generates comprehensive diagnostics. This includes extracting the obligation cause chain (stored in each Obligation struct), providing suggestions for adding trait bounds or imports, and explaining why specific impls don't apply. Additional specialized error reporting is in fulfillment_errors.rs for detailed trait compatibility analysis.\n\n**Cache and Performance**: The selection context maintains selection and evaluation caches (SelectionCache and EvaluationCache defined in compiler/rustc_middle/src/traits/select.rs lines 15-18) keyed on environment and trait predicates to avoid redundant candidate assembly and evaluation.\n\nThe entire chain ensures that trait obligations are resolved deterministically while detecting ambiguities, providing helpful error messages, and optimizing through caching and specialization."
